    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3896593>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Haasea musimontium (Strasser, 1937). A. Paralectotype female (MHNG), habitus, lateral view. B–E. Lectotype male (MHNG). B. Microslides with dissected parts. C. Posterior gonopods, anterior view. D. Left anterior gonopod, mesal view. E. Right anterior gonopod, lateral view. F. Lectotype male and paralectotype female (MHNG), habitus. Abbreviations: a—angiocoxite; ab—anterior branch; dp—distal part; mp—mesal process; pb—posterior branch; pc—papillated cone; pl—posterior lamella; plp—posterior lateral process; t—telopodite. Without scale. Photos credit: Peter Schwendinger." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3896593/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3896629>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. Distribution of the genus Haasea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3896629/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3896635>
    dc:description "FIGURE 41. Distribution of H. cyanopida (Attems, 1903), H. faucium (Verhoeff, 1931a), H. filicis (Verhoeff, 1929), H. gruberi sp. nov., H. musimontium (Strasser, 1937) and H. pretneri (Strasser, 1966)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3896635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

